" a macro that makes vimdo really easy to use
" simply record a macro with qq and then hit do
" your macro will automatically be saved in ~/vimdo.vim as a 'normal' command
" at that point you can automatically use the same macro to modify any text file by calling the vimdo command:
" 	vimdo file.txt
map do :split ~/vimdo.vimggVG"qpinormal :wq

